  <h2 class='section-heading'>Introduction</h2>
  <ol>
  <p>This website is home to the <strong>Web Archives for Longitudinal Knowledge (WALK) Project</strong>, an envisioned Canadian national Web Archiving portal. Spearheaded by the <a href="https://uwaterloo.ca/">University of Waterloo</a>, <a href="http://yorku.ca/">York University</a>, and the <a href="https://ualberta.ca/">University of Alberta</a>, we plan to bring together interested Canadian partners to provide access to their collections.</p>
  <p>Currently, this is a prototype site providing access to one such archive, the University of Toronto's Canadian Political Parties and Political Interest Groups collection. This website allows you to search content from 50 political parties and political interest groups, from October 2005 to March 2015.</strong></p>
